(418, 2, '2013-02-18 11:56:32', '2013-02-18 18:56:32', 'If you''re looking for a job in IT, you might want to check out the Kemtah Group''s virtual job fair. It starts today and runs for 30 days. Learn about the company and its jobs from the comfort of your home.  Jobs are available in Albuquerque and also in other major cities in the U.S\n\nTo access the virtual booth or register for the job fair in advance, <a href="http://www.redhired.com/functions/show/showindex-html.asp" target="_blank">click here</a>.', 'Kemtah Group holds its first online job fair', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kemtah-group-holds-its-first-online-job-fair', '', '', '2013-02-18 11:56:32', '2013-02-18 18:56:32', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=418', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(424, 2, '2013-02-25 12:56:08', '2013-02-25 19:56:08', 'The  Educators'' Job Fair at New Mexico State University is a two-day event, co-sponsored by the College of Education and coordinated by Career Services. The Educators’ Job Fair allows for candidates and numerous school districts located throughout the nation to discuss career options and employment opportunities in formal interviews.\n\nFor  information, please contact:\n\nElizabeth Ortega, Coordinator - Employer Relations, Career Services\nPhone: (575) 646-1631\nFax: (575) 646-5421\nE-mail: <a href="mailto:employer@nmsu.edu">employer@nmsu.edu</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Educators Job Fair April 22-23 Las Cruces', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'educators-job-fair-april-22-23-las-cruces', '', '', '2013-02-25 12:56:08', '2013-02-25 19:56:08', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=424', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(428, 2, '2013-03-04 15:11:47', '2013-03-04 22:11:47', 'A workshop on starting a small business, sponsored by the New Mexico Department of Workforce Solutions will be held on\n\nWednesday, March 6, 2013\n\n10:00 AM - 12:00 PM\n\nVeteran''s Procurement Assistance Center\n1314 Madeira SE\nAlbuquerque, NM 87108\n\nTo register, contact Stacy Sacco at 505-892-1238 or by email at <a href="mailto:ssacco@wesst.org">ssacco@wesst.org</a>', 'Starting a Small Business Workshop', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'starting-a-small-business-workshop', '', '', '2013-03-04 15:11:47', '2013-03-04 22:11:47', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=428', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(431, 2, '2013-03-11 22:43:46', '2013-03-12 04:43:46', 'According to the New Mexico Free Press, there are plenty of department store jobs out there, especially if you regularly check job boards for company openings you can also <a href="http://www.departmentstoreemployment.com">visit this website</a> which list numerous department store jobs. The department chains all require a constant supply of talent.\n<strong>Job Openings at Target in New Mexico</strong>\n<div>\n\n1) Currently there is a vacancy for a “Store Team Leader” in Roswell. The successful applicant will be responsible for managing 150 - 500 team members.\n2) The company is also looking for an “Executive Team Leader In Training” at its Farmington and Roswell locations.\n3) Finally, an “Executive Team Leader” is sought in Albuquerque.\n\n<strong>Job Openings at Walmart in New Mexico</strong>\n\nThe company currently is recruiting to fill 26 job openings in New Mexico. The job openings are primarily positions centered around management and customer service and you can apply by submitting a Walmart application. Walmart presently has vacancies for such jobs as follow:\n\n1) In Las Cruces the company needs a “Market Health and Wellness Director”, a “Doctor of Optometry” and a “Pre Grad Intern” for its pharmacy.\n2) For its location in Los Lunas, Walmart needs a “Lift Driver” to work in the warehouse, a “G Orderfiller DD” and a “G Orderfiller MP” and a “Pre Grad Intern” for its pharmacy.\n3) There are 3 opening in Rio Rancho. A “Staff Pharmacist” is required with a Bachelor’s Degree in Pharmacy; a “Pre Grad Intern” enrolled in an accredited Pharmacy school; as well as a “Market Asset Protection Manager” who coordinates job-related activities and assignments for asset protection.\n\n<strong>Job Openings at JCPenny in New Mexico</strong>\n\nJCPenny currently has 37 openings in New Mexico. The company is hiring an “Associate Salon Designer” in Albuquerque, Farmington, Las Cruces, Roswell and Gallup. It is filling a vacancy for the position of “Sephora Product Consultant” in Albuquerque in the Cottonwood Mall. The company is hiring “Service Specialists” in six locations.\n\n<strong>Job Openings at Kmart in New Mexico</strong>\n\nKmart is looking for a “Store Manager” and many other position you can apply by submitting a <a href="http://www.departmentstoreemployment.com/kmart-application/">Kmart application</a>. Store Managers are responsible for the entire operation of a store’s operations and merchandising. Their role is to increase profitability in their assigned locations. They also have an important role developing and training their staff to ensure that customer satisfaction is met according to store standards, as well as hiring new staff\n\n</div>', 'Department Store Jobs in New Mexico', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'department-store-jobs-in-new-mexico', '', '', '2013-03-11 22:43:46', '2013-03-12 04:43:46', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=431', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(436, 2, '2013-03-18 13:38:11', '2013-03-18 19:38:11', 'Now that the weather''s warming, and the days are longer, it''s time to shake off the winter doldrums, dust off that resume, and get serious about finding a better job. One of the things that holds people back is listening to their own internal critic. You know that voice, the one that says:\n\n"There''s nothing out there"\n\n"Unemployment is so high in my city, what''s the use?"\n\n"You''re too old to change careers"\n\n"There''s nothing in my field"\n\n"I''m too busy to look for another job"\n\nIf any of that sounds familiar, it''s time to have a talk with yourself.  No matter where you live or what the employment situation is, employers are always looking for bright, talented people to fill jobs.  Update your resume, develop a plan for what employers you''re interested in approaching, and think about who in your life you can contact about your job search. The most fruitful method of job searching is through personal contacts (informational interviewing), and spring is the best time of year to get going!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Spring is the Time to Get Serious About Your Job Search', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spring-is-the-time-to-get-serious-about-your-job-search', '', '', '2013-03-18 13:38:11', '2013-03-18 19:38:11', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=436', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(441, 2, '2013-03-27 17:23:55', '2013-03-27 23:23:55', 'Many times my clients start out strong in their job search efforts, but slowly lose momentum as the challenges of everyday life intervene.\n\nTo be successful in a career transition or job search, it''s important to have a plan with clearly delineated steps, clear goal and objectives, alternate methods of reaching your goals, and contingencies for when things go awry.\n\nAny method of record-keeping will work, as long as you''re faithful about keeping it up.  Paper, computer, calendar, whatever your preference, just be sure you''re keeping track of everything you''ve done and plan to do.\n\nSet goals for how many people you''ll contact this week.\n\nHow many research interviews will you do?  How many phone calls will it take to schedule those interviews?\n\nHow much research time will it take to decide what companies you will approach this week? this month?\n\nHow many resumes will you need if you are looking in more than one field?  Are you keeping track of which one you sent where?\n\nMost important, don''t let yourself get sidetracked by the demands of daily living. If you want a new job, you have to put in the effort, which takes time, diligence and creativity.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Consistency is the Key to Job Search Success', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'consistency-is-the-key-to-job-search-success', '', '', '2013-03-27 17:23:55', '2013-03-27 23:23:55', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=441', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(462, 2, '2013-04-08 13:36:25', '2013-04-08 19:36:25', 'I am often asked about how to incorporate keywords into a resume. This is the same question as how to tailor your skills and experience to meet the needs of the employer. Many large companies use competency-based job descriptions and behavioral interviewing to choose candidates. If you create a resume based on research into the position, you will be prepared for whatever comes your way.\n\nKeywords are simply the skills and abilities that an employer wants in a top candidate. If you are a computer programmer, important keywords are the software you are proficient with. If you are an editor, keywords relate to the type of documents you work with and the software you use. If you are an administrative assistant, keywords relate to software, office processes such as calendaring, and the machines you can operate.\n\nEvery position requires you to have knowledge, skills, and abilities. If you’re unsure how to describe these, there are many resources for you to use in your research. First, carefully read the entire job description. Next, read the company website for clues to what type of employee they value. Look on job boards for notices of similar jobs by the same company or the same industry.\n\nAs you write accomplishment statements for your resume, take everything you have learned into account, and use the language of the employer. If they want applicants with mediation experience, talk about how you have resolved problems. If they want independent decision-makers, talk about examples of how you’ve led teams or work groups.\n\nIf you need more help in writing about your skills and accomplishments, look at the website <a href="http://www.onetonline.org/">http://www.onetonline.org/</a>\n\nIt lists thousands of job descriptions including the tasks, skills, abilities, work activities, training needed, and salaries by state and nationally. It even includes information on the interests, work styles, and work values of people who are successful in that job. There is plenty of information to get the juices flowing so you can incorporate key words that will take your resume to the top of the pile.', 'Use Keywords to Get Your Resume Noticed', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'use-keywords-to-get-your-resume-noticed', '', '', '2013-04-08 13:36:25', '2013-04-08 19:36:25', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=462', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(467, 2, '2013-04-12 20:47:56', '2013-04-13 02:47:56', '<pre>The Ruidoso-New Mexico Workforce Connection Office, in partnership with\nENMU-Ruidoso announced will host a county-wide career and hiring event on\nMonday, April 15, from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the White Mountain Annex, 201\nWhite Mountain Drive.  For more information, go <a href="http://www.ruidosonews.com/ruidoso-business/ci_22988610/job-fair-coming-ruidoso" target="_blank">here.</a> \n\n</pre>', 'Job fair coming to Ruidoso 4/15', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'job-fair-coming-to-ruidoso-415', '', '', '2013-04-12 20:47:56', '2013-04-13 02:47:56', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=467', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(471, 2, '2013-04-16 15:35:15', '2013-04-16 21:35:15', 'A recent job fair in Albuquerque organized by New Mexico Workforce Connection was attended by 800 people and reported on krqe.com''s website. Job seekers reported feeling optimistic about their chances after attending the job fair.\n\nAt this job fair, around 40 different companies showcased their businesses, each with positions available.  Arthur Martinez, site manager for Workforce Connection in Albuquerque, said a wide variety of jobs were available from the professional to the service industry.\n\n“I''m seeing lot more activity in employers, and they''re interested in hiring,” said Martinez.  "Typically, New Mexico, we''re last entering the recession, and we''re late exiting, but I anticipate there''s some additional turnaround coming."\n\nThere is still a lot of competition on every position. Lockheed Martin is looking for call-center workers and said the interest is incredible.', 'Job-fair hopefuls see brighter prospects', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'job-fair-hopefuls-see-brighter-prospects', '', '', '2013-04-16 15:35:15', '2013-04-16 21:35:15', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=471', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(489, 2, '2013-05-06 20:24:00', '2013-05-07 02:24:00', 'NM lawmakers form group to study job creation\n<pre>SANTA FE, N.M. (AP) — Lawmakers are creating a task force to consider how\nNew Mexico can create more jobs in emerging and new industries. The\nLegislative Council agreed Tuesday to establish a "jobs council" that will\ninclude legislative leaders as ...\n&lt;<a href="http://www.businessweek.com/ap/2013-05-01/nm-lawmakers-form-group-to-study-job-creation" target="_blank">http://www.businessweek.com/ap/2013-05-01/nm-lawmakers-form-group-to-study-job-creation</a>&gt;</pre>', 'New Mexico Lawmakers study Job Creation', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-mexico-lawmakers-study-job-creation', '', '', '2013-05-06 20:24:00', '2013-05-07 02:24:00', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=489', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(493, 2, '2013-05-10 20:30:25', '2013-05-11 02:30:25', '<pre>Sitel, a leading global customer care provider,announced the addition of 200 \nfull-time positions and 150 temporary positions for its customer care call center \nin Albuquerque, New Mexico. In December, Sitel Albuquerque expanded the 1(st) floor of its\n 45,000 square foot facility, adding an additional 320 seats. The growth is due to \nexpanding volume with its clients, a Global Beverage Company and Global Satellite TV \nProvider. Newly hired Albuquerque associates will provide inbound customer care support. \nThe temporary positions will provide a great opportunity to learn the business and those\nhired in temporary positions may be eligible for future positions.\n\nSitel is working closely with the New Mexico Department of Workforce\nSolutions and hosting onsite job fairs on Wednesday, May 15(th) from 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. at the company''s facility\nat 4420 The 25 Way.\n&lt;<a href="http://online.wsj.com/article/PR-CO-20130503-909279.html" target="_blank">http://online.wsj.com/article/PR-CO-20130503-909279.html</a>&gt;</pre>', 'Sitel to Host Job Fair and Hire 350 Customer Care Positions', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sitel-to-host-job-fair-and-hire-350-customer-care-positions', '', '', '2013-05-10 20:30:25', '2013-05-11 02:30:25', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=493', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(512, 2, '2013-05-21 09:21:34', '2013-05-21 15:21:34', '<div id="story_text" itemprop="articleBody">\n\nFrom the Albuquerque Journal May 20\n\nThe Department of Workforce Solutions reports that New Mexico''s unemployment rate dropped last month and that job growth has improved.\n\nState officials said Friday the seasonally adjusted unemployment rate was 6.7 percent in April. That''s down from 6.9 percent in March and 7 percent in April 2012.\n\nNew Mexico has gained about 7,900 jobs during the past 12 months, for a 1 percent growth rate.\n\nIt''s been five years since the state''s employment growth was at or exceeded 1 percent, and the department said the state''s economy "may be gathering momentum as we start a sustained recovery."\n\nState officials said nine industries have gained jobs and three have lost jobs since April 2012. The construction industry has picked up 1,800 jobs, which is its best performance since 2006.\n\n</div>\n<strong>Think your friends should see this? Share it with them!</strong>', 'New Mexico Gaining Jobs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-mexico-gaining-jobs', '', '', '2013-05-21 09:21:34', '2013-05-21 15:21:34', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=512', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(530, 2, '2013-06-24 20:42:04', '2013-06-25 02:42:04', '<pre>\nHispanicBusiness.com reports that New Mexico gained \n7,800 jobs between May 2012 and May 2013, and the\nAlbuquerque metropolitan statistical area added \n4,400 jobs year-over-year,\nthe state Workforce Solutions Department reported Friday. \n\nFor more information, go <a href="http://www.hispanicbusiness.com/2013/6/24/solid_job_growth_seen_in_new.htm" target="_blank">here</a>. \n\n</pre>', 'Solid Job Growth Seen in New Mexico', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'solid-job-growth-seen-in-new-mexico', '', '', '2013-06-24 20:42:04', '2013-06-25 02:42:04', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=530', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(535, 2, '2013-07-01 20:20:06', '2013-07-02 02:20:06', 'Albuquerque Business First reports that, New Mexico is slowly regaining its lost construction jobs. However, the number of construction jobs in New Mexico is still sitting at 16,000 below its peak level.\n\nThe state’s peak came during the boom of 2006, and in June of that year New Mexico had 59,600 construction jobs. In May of this year, the total was 43,600 — down 16,000, or 27 percent. New Mexico did gain 500 construction jobs last month and has been on a steady if modest gain for the year, adding 2,900 construction jobs since January as the housing market slowly continues its recovery in the Albuquerque area and other areas of the state.\n\nThe data comes from an analysis of U.S. Labor Department data by the Associated General Contractors of America.', 'New Mexico Gaining Construction Jobs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-mexico-gaining-construction-jobs', '', '', '2013-07-01 20:20:06', '2013-07-02 02:20:06', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=535', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(539, 2, '2013-07-19 12:50:39', '2013-07-19 18:50:39', 'Presbyterian Health Plan is hiring for Medicaid ramp-up.   They will hold an open house and job fair  on July 25 to hire 30 to 40 people to serve its Medicaid membership.\n\nThe job fair will be held at the Embassy Suites hotel near I-25 and Lomas in Albuquerque,\nFor more information, go <a href="http://www.bizjournals.com/albuquerque/blog/morning-edition/2013/07/presbyterian-hiring-for-medicaid-ramp-up.html" target="_blank">here. </a>', 'Presbyterian Health Plan is Hiring', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'presbyterian-health-plan-is-hiring', '', '', '2013-07-19 12:50:39', '2013-07-19 18:50:39', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=539', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(546, 2, '2013-08-17 21:19:37', '2013-08-18 03:19:37', 'Check out American''s Worst Companies to work for as surveyed by 24/7 Wall Street. You might be surprised!  DISH and Express Scripts lead the pack.\n\nRead the whole article<a href="http://247wallst.com/special-report/2013/07/19/americas-worst-companies-to-work-for-2/2/" target="_blank"> here. </a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Worst Companies In America to Work For', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'worst-companies-in-america-to-work-for', '', '', '2013-08-17 21:19:37', '2013-08-18 03:19:37', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=546', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(553, 2, '2013-08-22 21:03:21', '2013-08-23 03:03:21', 'Two major job fairs will be happening in Albuquerque starting on Monday.\n\nThe first will be for the next Gordman''s store set to open near the Coronado Center in Uptown Albuquerque. Company representatives expect to hire about 100 new employees for that location.\n\nThe job fair will be held with the help of the New Mexico Workforce Connection. This will be from 8 a.m. to 7 p.m. at the New Mexico Workforce Connection Office at 501 Mountain Road in Northeast Albuquerque. <a href="http://www.gordmans.com/Careers" target="_blank">www.gordmans.com/Careers</a>\n\nThe second job fair is held by Sodexo UNM Sports and Leisure. This organization will be looking for 40 new servers who will handle the food and beverage services for the upcoming games for Lobo Football and Basketball season.\n\nTheir job fair runs from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. at the McDavid Lounge on the southside of the Pit.', 'Job Fairs in ABQ on Monday', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'job-fairs-in-abq-on-monday', '', '', '2013-08-22 21:03:21', '2013-08-23 03:03:21', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=553', 0, 'post', '', 0);
