/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="51" Name="List Table 6 Colorful Accent 4"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="52" Name="List Table 7 Colorful Accent 4"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="46" Name="List Table 1 Light Accent 5"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="47" Name="List Table 2 Accent 5"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="48" Name="List Table 3 Accent 5"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="49" Name="List Table 4 Accent 5"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="50" Name="List Table 5 Dark Accent 5"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="51" Name="List Table 6 Colorful Accent 5"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="52" Name="List Table 7 Colorful Accent 5"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="46" Name="List Table 1 Light Accent 6"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="47" Name="List Table 2 Accent 6"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="48" Name="List Table 3 Accent 6"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="49" Name="List Table 4 Accent 6"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="50" Name="List Table 5 Dark Accent 6"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="51" Name="List Table 6 Colorful Accent 6"/>\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="52" Name="List Table 7 Colorful Accent 6"/>\n</w:LatentStyles>\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 10]>\n\n<style>\n /* Style Definitions */\ntable.MsoNormalTable\n{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";\nmso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\nmso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\nmso-style-noshow:yes;\nmso-style-priority:99;\nmso-style-parent:"";\nmso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\nmso-para-margin:0in;\nmso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\nfont-size:10.0pt;\nfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}\n</style><![endif]-->\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0in;">Is your creative side withering on the vine? Do you spend too much time working and not enough time writing that novel you''ve always wanted to write? Do you have fantasies about putting your knowledge into an e-book that you''re sure the world is waiting for?</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0in;"> If you need some help opening up your creativity or would like an objective opinion from an editor and published writer about a writing project, I offer classes through The University of New Mexico Continuing Education and also individual consultation and coaching for aspiring writers. Fiction and nonfiction.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0in;"> Contact me at <a href="mailto:info@compassrosecareers.com">info@compassrosecareers.com</a> or phone (505-235-9753) to discuss your project. For consultation, my hourly rate of $45/hour applies. For longer editing projects, I can usually give you a flat fee.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">  </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0in;">The world of publishing is changing fast, and there''s no better time to be putting your work out there!</p>', 'Consulting and Coaching Services for Writers', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'consulting-and-coaching-services-for-writers', '', '', '2013-09-07 17:01:39', '2013-09-07 23:01:39', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=567', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(582, 2, '2013-10-14 16:16:01', '2013-10-14 22:16:01', 'Canon, manufacturer of cameras and printers, is opening a new tech support center in Albuquerque in Spring, 2014. They expect to hire 150 people.  The company will be located in the Jefferson industrial corridor.\n\nFor more information, go <a href="http://www.kob.com/article/stories/S3184563.shtml?cat=500" target="_blank">here. </a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Canon Coming to Albuquerque with Tech Support Jobs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'canon-coming-to-albuquerque-with-tech-support-jobs', '', '', '2013-10-14 16:16:01', '2013-10-14 22:16:01', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=582', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(590, 2, '2014-07-02 15:26:10', '2014-07-02 21:26:10', 'You lost your job. Got laid off. The company closed. Unemployment isn''t enough. What do you do?\n\nChoosing a new direction can be difficult. If you liked your old job, you may try to find one exactly like it. If your research shows there are opportunities for people with your skills and experience, then your task is simpler. Not easy, but simpler. Polish up that resume. Network with everyone you know. Get your resume in front of decision makers. Settle in for a concentrated and targeted job search.\n\nIf you didn''t like what you were doing, or if the industry is declining, it may be time to look at something entirely different.\n\n<b>But how do you choose? </b>\n\nSome people look at what''s available. What jobs have the most openings, or pay the most. Sometimes that works, but often it backfires. Just because you know you can work as a nurse or a respiratory therapist doesn''t mean you will enjoy the work, the environment or the people you will be working with.\n\n<b>So, again, how do you choose?</b>\n\nFirst you must know your skills, interests, and abilities and have a pretty good sense of the type of problems you want to solve.\n\nBut if you''ve gone through a self-assessment and feel pretty confident about what you’ve got to offer, the next thing is motivation.\n\n<strong>Why do you want a job?</strong> Well, obviously, to make a living. But beyond that, people are motivated by different desires.\n\n<b>Do you want security?</b> A steady paycheck? Lifetime employment? Regular hours.\n\n<b>Do you want the chance to achieve and be successful in an organization? </b>These jobs require longer hours, are often more demanding, and are found in every industry.\n\n<b>Do you want independence above all? </b>You might be an entrepreneur, but be sure you''re willing to work very, very hard to make a living.\n\n<b>Do you want to offer service? </b>Opportunities abound in the not for profit sector, from entry level clerical to directors of agencies, but be prepared for lower wages, long hours, and be sure you''re willing to guard against burnout.\n\n<b>Do you want to express your creativity? </b>The arts may be for you. The good news is that opportunities exist in business, government, and not for profits.', 'How To Choose a New Career', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-choose-a-new-career', '', '', '2014-07-02 15:26:10', '2014-07-02 21:26:10', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=590', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(593, 2, '2014-07-07 16:28:23', '2014-07-07 22:28:23', '<h4>The New Mexico Economic Development Department''s Job Training Incentive Program (JTIP) Board approved $708,167 in funding at its June meeting to seven companies that will create 99 jobs around New Mexico with an average wage of $15.20.</h4>\n<h4>Some of the companies involved inclue Neptune Aviation Services of Alamorgordo, Santa Fe Spirits of Santa Fe, PreCheck, Inc of Alamogordo, and CAaNES, LLC of Albuququerque.</h4>\n<h4>To qualify, new or expanding companies must either create a product in New Mexico, or provide a non-retail service with 50 percent of the company''s costumer or revenue base outside of the state. The eligible jobs must be full-time and year-round. The trainee must be a new hire to the company and have been a New Mexico resident for at least one year at any time prior to being hired. For more information on JTIP, visit <a href="http://www.gonm.biz/">www.goNM.biz</a>.</h4>', 'Job Incentive Program Coming to New Mexico', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'job-incentive-program-coming-to-new-mexico', '', '', '2014-07-07 16:28:23', '2014-07-07 22:28:23', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=593', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(597, 2, '2014-07-14 08:34:20', '2014-07-14 14:34:20', 'The iconic U.S. brand Indian Motorcycles is back and coming to its first New Mexico dealership later this year.\n\nBusiness partners and cousins Michael Gaillour and Louis Herrera purchased a 9,000-square-foot building at 4509 Alameda Blvd NE, (on the corner of Alameda and Washington) where they will open Indian Motorcycle of Albuquerque this fall.\n\nIn addition to motorcycle sales and service, the dealership will offer Indian Motorcycle parts, apparel, and accessories.\n\nBoth the architect and the principal contractor are New Mexico firms. James B. Clark of Masterworks Architects designed the build-out and the principal contractor is Damian J. Chimenti of Insight Construction.\n\nIndian Motorcycle of Albuquerque is owned by cousins Louis Herrera and Michael Gaillour, native New Mexicans who grew up in Questa. Herrera graduated from New Mexico Highlands University in Las Vegas, New Mexico, and earned a Master’s degree from Purdue University. He also attended Darmouth College. He served in the U.S. Army and is currently a Lt. Colonel and battalion commander in the New Mexico National Guard. Gaillour graduated from the University of New Mexico with a degree in finance and has had a 30-year banking career. To learn more, please visit <a href="https://www.facebook.com/IndianMotorcycleABQ" target="_blank">facebook.com/IndianMotorcycleABQ</a>.', 'Indian Motorcyles Coming to Albuquerque', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'indian-motorcyles-coming-to-albuquerque', '', '', '2014-07-14 08:34:20', '2014-07-14 14:34:20', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=597', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(599, 2, '2014-07-10 08:39:23', '2014-07-10 14:39:23', 'Although the Albuquerque metro area’s jobs picture remains bleak, the oil patch in southeast New Mexico and in Hobbs is booming. Now economic development officials in the area are hoping to lure Albuquerque workers.\n\nOn July 6, the Hobbs Chamber of Commerce placed an ad in the Sunday Albuquerque Journal for its <a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/pagead/adview?ai=BOrAhfSG7U9HRGIXfpAOyjoLACtmrg6oFAAAAEAEgqZbaHzgAWPmSw66zAWDJ_v2KuKTcGLIBE3d3dy5iaXpqb3VybmFscy5jb226AQlnZnBfaW1hZ2XIAQnaAWZodHRwOi8vd3d3LmJpempvdXJuYWxzLmNvbS9hbGJ1cXVlcnF1ZS9uZXdzLzIwMTQvMDcvMDcvbW9yZS1ob3VzaW5nLWpvYnMtZnVlbGluZy1ob2Jicy1kZW1hbmQtZm9yLmh0bWyYAui2AcACAuACAOoCGS80NjM1L2J6ai5hbGJ1cXVlcnF1ZS9vb3D4Av7RHpAD6AKYA-ADqAMB4AQBkgULCAcQARgBIIHx7RigBiA&amp;sigh=2K1p_gW12k8&amp;adurl=http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/imgad?id=CICAgKDjlbfH_QEQARgBMgj5VW-uioso5g%26t%3D10%26cT%3Dhttp%253A//bizjournals.com%26l%3Dhttp%253A//hobbschamber.chambermaster.com/jobs" target="_blank">Hobbs Jobs website </a>in the hope of luring Albuquerqueans and other New Mexicans to move to the oil patch.\n\n<a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/pagead/adview?ai=BOrAhfSG7U9HRGIXfpAOyjoLACtmrg6oFAAAAEAEgqZbaHzgAWPmSw66zAWDJ_v2KuKTcGLIBE3d3dy5iaXpqb3VybmFscy5jb226AQlnZnBfaW1hZ2XIAQnaAWZodHRwOi8vd3d3LmJpempvdXJuYWxzLmNvbS9hbGJ1cXVlcnF1ZS9uZXdzLzIwMTQvMDcvMDcvbW9yZS1ob3VzaW5nLWpvYnMtZnVlbGluZy1ob2Jicy1kZW1hbmQtZm9yLmh0bWyYAui2AcACAuACAOoCGS80NjM1L2J6ai5hbGJ1cXVlcnF1ZS9vb3D4Av7RHpAD6AKYA-ADqAMB4AQBkgULCAcQARgBIIHx7RigBiA&amp;sigh=2K1p_gW12k8&amp;adurl=http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/imgad?id=CICAgKDjlbfH_QEQARgBMgj5VW-uioso5g%26t%3D10%26cT%3Dhttp%253A//bizjournals.com%26l%3Dhttp%253A//hobbschamber.chambermaster.com/jobs" target="_blank">The Hobbs Jobs site</a> has more than 30 jobs listed, including positions for accountants, civil engineers, survey crew chiefs, electro maintenance techs, cooks and casino marketing managers.\n\n“We need builders here in Hobbs. If it is slow in Albuquerque, we would love to have Albuquerque builders build apartments in Hobbs, and our city has a really good incentive program to work with on that.”', 'Oil Field Jobs in Hobbs, NM', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oil-field-jobs-in-hobbs-nm', '', '', '2014-07-10 08:39:23', '2014-07-10 14:39:23', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=599', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(603, 2, '2014-10-09 16:40:12', '2014-10-09 22:40:12', 'The State Economic Development Department will be footing an estimated $1 million to help build sewer and water lines at the Moriarty Airport where Google is constructing a nearly 60,000-square-foot building.\n\nGoogle is looking to use the airport to develop solar-powered drones.The drones would fly at nearly 65,000 feet, providing communication services for rural areas. Before the Internet giant came to town, Titan Aerospace only had a few hangars and temporary offices.\n\n<span style="line-height: 19.5px;">More than 200 aviation-related jobs are expected to come to Moriarity as a result of Google''s presence, </span>\n\n&nbsp;\nRead more: <a href="http://www.koat.com/news/moriartys-partnership-with-google-may-bring-200-jobs/28202144#ixzz3FgptrHoD">http://www.koat.com/news/moriartys-partnership-with-google-may-bring-200-jobs/28202144#ixzz3FgptrHoD</a>', 'Google to Bring Jobs to Moriarity', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'google-to-bring-jobs-to-moriarity', '', '', '2014-10-09 16:40:12', '2014-10-09 22:40:12', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=603', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(610, 2, '2014-10-09 17:25:46', '2014-10-09 23:25:46', '<h2>What tools do you need to do a job search in a tight market?</h2>\nAlthough much of the U.S. is pulling out of the unemployment slump, New Mexico is still experiencing high unemployment. There are signs that is changing.  We were the last to fall into recession, and we may be the last to cimb out, but while the situation is improving, it''s still important to use every resource at your disposal.\n<h3>The most important tool is your resume and cover letter</h3>\nBoth documents must be up to date, professionally written, focus on skills, achievements and the results that employers can expect you to provide.  If you are in doubt, get feedback on your document and be sure that you''re not writing in jargon, old-fashioned language, or anything that sounds like a job description copied from the Internet.\n<h3>Your Online Presence Counts</h3>\nMany employers Google potential employees. They check Facebook, Linked In, Twitter and other social media sites.  If you are a professional in any field, or your job involves software or hardware, be sure that your online presence is up-to-date, professional, and persusive. If you don''t know how to do that, get help from someone who does.\n<h3>Your Elevator Speech is Critical</h3>\nNamed for the mythical ride up the elevator with the CEO of the company you''re interested in, the elevator speech is a short summary of your skills, education, and qualifications for the job. In an interview, it may be phrased as: "Tell me about yourself", "Why are you interested in this job?",  "Why should I hire you?" or something related,  Be sure you can easily talk about the main points that qualify you for the position.\n<h3>Yes, Research Matters</h3>\nThe more you know about a company, its history, strengths, weaknesses, mergers, hiring patterns, and brand, the more motivated an applicant you will appear to be. The time to research any company you land an interview with is more than worth the time you spend,', 'To Find a New Job, Be Creative', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'to-find-a-new-job-be-creative', '', '', '2014-10-09 17:25:46', '2014-10-09 23:25:46', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=610', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(619, 2, '2014-10-13 16:34:20', '2014-10-13 22:34:20', '&nbsp;\n<h4><strong>Eleven community colleges in New Mexico will receive federal funding</strong> to provide innovative training programs, in partnership with local businesses, to help New Mexican adults advance into high-wage careers.</h4>\n<h4><a href="http://www.myhighplains.com/story/d/story/new-mexico-community-colleges-receive-federal-fund/11414/-ilbAlMw7EqLw3YJ1WyL5Q" target="_blank">The funding</a>, provided under Trade Adjustment Assistance Community College and Career Training (TAACCCT) competitive grant program, will allow these community colleges to expand and improve their ability to deliver education and career training programs that will help job seekers get the skills they need for in-demand jobs in New Mexicos health care industry.</h4>\n<h4> This funding will allow colleges across New Mexico to provide workers with quality job training to help fill New Mexicos expanding health care and technology workforce needs,</h4>\n<div style="text-align: center;">****</div>\n<div style="text-align: center;"></div>\n<h4 style="text-align: left;"><strong>AerSale</strong>, an international supplier of aftermarket aircraft, will create 50 new jobs at the Roswell, New Mexico, International Air Center. The firm currently employs 100 workers in Roswell. The firm will begin hiring 30 certified aircraft technicians and 20 additional support personnel.</h4>\n<h4>The Roswell International Air Center has a 13,000 foot runway that accommodates major aircraft manufacturers. Roswell''s Air Center is also ideal for aircraft storage and maintenance, and can accommodate up to 800 aircraft.</h4>', 'NM Community Colleges Get Funding for Job Training', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nm-community-colleges-get-funding-for-job-training', '', '', '2014-10-13 16:34:20', '2014-10-13 22:34:20', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=619', 0, 'post', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(622, 2, '2014-10-20 16:08:00', '2014-10-20 22:08:00', 'A Delaware company announced Thursday it will invest $52 million in a truck-to-rail facility in Milan to help move oil from the Four Corners region to market.\n\nNLG Energy Partners’ facility will create 62 jobs initially and another 50 or so within five years, according to the state Economic Development Department.\n\nMost of the jobs will be New Mexico-based truck driving positions, and wages overall will average $92,000 a year plus benefits, said Angela Heisel, spokeswoman for the state Economic Development Department.\n\nCibola County will receive $1.2 million in Local Economic Development Act funds from the state to help with capital expenses on the project, Heisel said.\n\nOil trucked from the Four Corners area will be loaded into rail tankers at the facility, from which it can be shipped elsewhere.\n\nOperations at the Milan truck offloading/rail loading facility are expected to begin in the third quarter of 2015.\n\n“New Mexico is geographically positioned to become a leading logistics hub and we’d like to see this region replicate the success that’s taking place at our southern border with the location of Union Pacific there,” Gov. Susana Martinez said in announcing the facility.', 'High Paying Trucking Jobs Coming to Milan NM', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'high-paying-trucking-jobs-coming-to-milan-nm', '', '', '2014-10-20 16:08:00', '2014-10-20 22:08:00', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=622', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(626, 2, '2015-01-05 15:50:46', '2015-01-05 22:50:46', 'It''s been a long time coming and we still have a long way to go, but 2014 saw positive job growth after years of shrinkage and stagnation, while neighboring states bounced back faster.\n\nStatewide, more than 14,000 new jobs were created this year – 700 of them in construction, which had been absolutely crushed during the recession.\n\nThe biggest gains were in education, which grew even during the hard times, and health care. Between the two, the sectors gained more than 6000 new jobs in 2014.\n\nThe manufacturing sector is still losing jobs, however – losing 1500 statewide this year. 600 government jobs also went away this year, as most of the job growth in New Mexico has come in the private sector.\n\nSo, if you''re looking, focus your job search efforts toward the more robust private sector. However, if you have specialized managerial or technical skills, even government may be a likely target.  The most effective job search is multi-pronged, leaving nothing out.', 'Job Growth Up in New Mexico', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'job-growth-up-in-new-mexico', '', '', '2015-01-05 15:50:46', '2015-01-05 22:50:46', '', 0, 'http://compassrosecareers.com/?p=626', 0, 'post', '', 0);
